Phase 0: Foundation & Setup (Sprint 0 - 2 Weeks)

Week 1: Environment Setup & Architecture

Day 1-2:
  - Create solution structure (Clean Architecture/Onion)
  - Set up Git repository with branching strategy (GitFlow)
  - Configure CI/CD pipeline (Azure DevOps/GitHub Actions)
  - Set up development environments (Dev, Test, Staging, Prod)

Day 3-4:
  - Database design (initial Entity Framework Core setup)
  - Authentication/Authorization foundation (ASP.NET Identity)
  - Multi-tenancy architecture design
  - Logging and monitoring setup (Serilog, Application Insights)

Day 5:
  - Project templates and code generation tools
  - Coding standards and review process
  - Documentation repository setup
  - Sprint planning for Sprint 1

Week 2: Core Infrastructure

Day 1-2:
  - Implement base entities and repositories
  - Set up Unit of Work pattern with Entity Framework
  - Create generic services and base controllers
  - Implement global exception handling

Day 3-4:
  - Configure email service (SendGrid/SMTP)
  - Set up file storage (Azure Blob Storage/AWS S3)
  - Implement caching layer (Redis/MemoryCache)
  - Configure CORS and security headers

Day 5:
  - API versioning strategy
  - Swagger/OpenAPI documentation
  - Postman collection creation
  - Performance testing baseline

Phase 1: User Management & Authentication (Sprints 1-2)

Sprint 1: Multi-Tenant Authentication

Epic: User Registration & Authentication
Stories:
  1. User registration (applicant, company admin)
  2. Email verification system
  3. Login/logout functionality
  4. Forgot password/reset password
  5. Multi-tenant user isolation
  6. Basic profile management
  7. Role-based authorization (applicant, admin, hr, manager)
  8. Session management

Technical Tasks:
  - Extend ASP.NET Identity with custom fields
  - JWT token implementation for API
  - Refresh token mechanism
  - Audit logging for user actions
  - Rate limiting on authentication endpoints

Sprint 2: Company Setup & Admin Dashboard

